◆ do_jobctl_trap()

static void do_jobctl_trap ( void  )
static

do_jobctl_trap - take care of ptrace jobctl traps

When PT_SEIZED, it's used for both group stop and explicit SEIZE/INTERRUPT traps. Both generate PTRACE_EVENT_STOP trap with accompanying siginfo. If stopped, lower eight bits of exit_code contain the stop signal; otherwise, SIGTRAP.

When !PT_SEIZED, it's used only for group stop trap with stop signal number as exit_code and no siginfo.

CONTEXT: Must be called with ->sighand->siglock held, which may be released and re-acquired before returning with intervening sleep.

◆ do_notify_parent_cldstop()

static void do_notify_parent_cldstop ( struct task_struct *  tsk,
bool  for_ptracer,
int  why 
)
static

do_notify_parent_cldstop - notify parent of stopped/continued state change : task reporting the state change : the notification is for ptracer : CLD_{CONTINUED|STOPPED|TRAPPED} to report

Notify 's parent that the stopped/continued state has changed. If is false, 's group leader notifies to its real parent. If true, reports to ->parent which should be the ptracer.

CONTEXT: Must be called with tasklist_lock at least read locked.

◆ do_signal_stop()

static bool do_signal_stop ( int  signr) & -> sighand->siglock)
static

do_signal_stop - handle group stop for SIGSTOP and other stop signals : signr causing group stop if initiating

If JOBCTL_STOP_PENDING is not set yet, initiate group stop with and participate in it. If already set, participate in the existing group stop. If participated in a group stop (and thus slept), true is returned with siglock released.

If ptraced, this function doesn't handle stop itself. Instead, JOBCTL_TRAP_STOP is scheduled and false is returned with siglock untouched. The caller must ensure that INTERRUPT trap handling takes places afterwards.

CONTEXT: Must be called with ->sighand->siglock held, which is released on true return.

RETURNS: false if group stop is already cancelled or ptrace trap is scheduled. true if participated in group stop.

◆ ptrace_trap_notify()

static void ptrace_trap_notify ( struct task_struct *  t)
static

ptrace_trap_notify - schedule trap to notify ptracer : tracee wanting to notify tracer

This function schedules sticky ptrace trap which is cleared on the next TRAP_STOP to notify ptracer of an event. must have been seized by ptracer.

If is running, STOP trap will be taken. If trapped for STOP and ptracer is listening for events, tracee is woken up so that it can re-trap for the new event. If trapped otherwise, STOP trap will be eventually taken without returning to userland after the existing traps are finished by PTRACE_CONT.

CONTEXT: Must be called with ->sighand->siglock held.

void task_clear_jobctl_pending ( struct task_struct *  task,

task_clear_jobctl_pending - clear jobctl pending bits : target task : pending bits to clear

Clear from ->jobctl. must be subset of JOBCTL_PENDING_MASK. If JOBCTL_STOP_PENDING is being cleared, other STOP bits are cleared together.

If clearing of leaves no stop or trap pending, this function calls task_clear_jobctl_trapping().

CONTEXT: Must be called with ->sighand->siglock held.

◆ task_clear_jobctl_trapping()

void task_clear_jobctl_trapping ( struct task_struct *  task)

task_clear_jobctl_trapping - clear jobctl trapping bit : target task

If JOBCTL_TRAPPING is set, a ptracer is waiting for us to enter TRACED. Clear it and wake up the ptracer. Note that we don't need any further locking. ->siglock guarantees that ->parent points to the ptracer.

CONTEXT: Must be called with ->sighand->siglock held.

◆ task_participate_group_stop()

static bool task_participate_group_stop ( struct task_struct *  task)
static

task_participate_group_stop - participate in a group stop : task participating in a group stop

has JOBCTL_STOP_PENDING set and is participating in a group stop. Group stop states are cleared and the group stop count is consumed if JOBCTL_STOP_CONSUME was set. If the consumption completes the group stop, the appropriate SIGNAL_* flags are set.

CONTEXT: Must be called with ->sighand->siglock held.

RETURNS: true if group stop completion should be notified to the parent, false otherwise.

◆ task_set_jobctl_pending()

bool task_set_jobctl_pending ( struct task_struct *  task,
unsigned long  mask 
)

task_set_jobctl_pending - set jobctl pending bits : target task : pending bits to set

Clear from ->jobctl. must be subset of JOBCTL_PENDING_MASK | JOBCTL_STOP_CONSUME | JOBCTL_STOP_SIGMASK | JOBCTL_TRAPPING. If stop signo is being set, the existing signo is cleared. If is already being killed or exiting, this function becomes noop.

CONTEXT: Must be called with ->sighand->siglock held.

RETURNS: true if is set, false if made noop because was dying.
